import React from 'react'
  import { MDXTag } from '@mdx-js/tag'
  import { RootStore } from "./RootStore"
import { Playground, PropsTable } from "docz"

export default ({components, ...props}) => <MDXTag name="wrapper"  components={components}>
<MDXTag name="h1" components={components} props={{"id":"root-store"}}>{`Root Store`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"store"}}>{`Store`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h3" components={components} props={{"id":"this-is-the-base-store-where-you-can-access-all-other-stores"}}>{`This is the base store where you can access all other stores.`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="hr" components={components}></MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`First, this store grabs the user. The store then uses the information of the user to determine what boxes, departments, etc. the user will see. All other stores are accessed through RootStore.`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`This store accesses the`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="ul" components={components}>
<MDXTag name="li" components={components} parentName="ul">{`User`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="li" components={components} parentName="ul">{`Checkout Store`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="li" components={components} parentName="ul">{`User Store`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="li" components={components} parentName="ul">{`UI Store`}</MDXTag>
</MDXTag></MDXTag>
